    "client_msg_id": "02c96c67-ec5e-48cd-8a98-c1b4c7391caf",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Greetings, ah, Earthlings\n\nMy name is Ryan, I caught on to this community via the podcast episode with Ella Hoeppner, the generative art in particular caught my attention.\n\nMy background is in astronomy, I previously worked at the VLA and on JWST (glad THAT one went well). These days I do a lot of software development with image processing and computer vision.\n\nI've been working on an image-based personal search engine for about 4 years now. I didn't know at the time I started it, but it's sorta kinda... very much like Vannevar Bush's Memex. It is a commercial project - happy to share it if that's appropriate.\n\nOutside of that, I've been making a lot of tiny programs lately - a webpage that <https://foxrow.com/wordle|always shows me yesterday's wordle>, a random-background-wallpaper-grabber (feels like getting a new computer!), putting <https://simonwillison.net/2020/Oct/9/git-scraping/|this data tracking technique> by Simon Willison (of Django fame) into practice.\n\nGlad to be here, and I'm happy to chat if any of that sounds interesting!",
    "user": "U0391QBSF9C",
    "ts": "1648607437.670199",
