                "type": "text",
                "text": "Greetings, ah, Earthlings\n\nMy name is Ryan, I caught on to this community via the podcast episode with Ella Hoeppner, the generative art in particular caught my attention.\n\nMy background is in astronomy, I previously worked at the VLA and on JWST (glad THAT one went well). These days I do a lot of software development with image processing and computer vision.\n\nI've been working on an image-based personal search engine for about 4 years now. I didn't know at the time I started it, but it's sorta kinda... very much like Vannevar Bush's Memex. It is a commercial project - happy to share it if that's appropriate.\n\nOutside of that, I've been making a lot of tiny programs lately - a webpage that "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://foxrow.com/wordle",
                "text": "always shows me yesterday's wordle"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", a random-background-wallpaper-grabber (feels like getting a new computer!), putting "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://simonwillison.net/2020/Oct/9/git-scraping/",
                "text": "this data tracking technique"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " by Simon Willison (of Django fame) into practice.\n\nGlad to be here, and I'm happy to chat if any of that sounds interesting!"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
