    "type": "message",
    "text": "Rego was inspired by <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Datalog|Datalog>, which is a well understood, decades old query language. Rego extends Datalog to support structured document models such as JSON.\n\nRego queries are assertions on data stored in OPA. These queries can be used to define policies that enumerate instances of data that violate the expected state of the system.\n\n<https://www.openpolicyagent.org/docs/latest/policy-language/>",
    "user": "UBN9AFS0N",
    "ts": "1648632029.299609",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
